An Eastern EuropeanViktor Navorsky is visiting New York. When he arrived at Kennedy Airport,in his homeland breaks out a war.
He can not fly back and may not enter with his current Papers into the U.S.
Viktor improvises and makes Kennedy Airport for months a temporary home,
where he looks at the people and falls in love with stewardess Amelia.
